# Local GitHub CLI setup

- GitHub CLI is installed on this machine through winget package `GitHub.cli`.
- Installed executable path: `C:\Program Files\GitHub CLI\gh.exe`.
- If `gh` is not found in the current PowerShell session, use the full executable path:

```powershell
& 'C:\Program Files\GitHub CLI\gh.exe' --version
& 'C:\Program Files\GitHub CLI\gh.exe' auth status
& 'C:\Program Files\GitHub CLI\gh.exe' pr create --draft --base develop --head <branch> --title '<title>' --body '<body>'
```

- A new terminal session should usually pick up the PATH update from the installer.
- For `eomdev-ai/phoenix`, prefer `gh` for PR creation/checks when available, then fall back to local GitHub credentials + REST only if `gh` is unavailable or unauthenticated.
